#: index.docbook:2
msgid "The &kword; Screen"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:5
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:7
msgid ""
"&kword;, like most <acronym>GUI</acronym>"
" based programs, divides the screen up into several areas. Each area of the "
"screen is used to perform a group of similar features . When you start the "
"&kword; screen, it is initially divided into 4 major areas:"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:12
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"kde-frame\">The &kde; titlebar</link> (which remains at the "
"top of all programs run under &kde;)."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:12
msgid "<link linkend=\"da\">The Menu Bar</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:12
msgid "<link linkend=\"mb\">an assortment of Toolbars</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:12
msgid "<link linkend=\"tb\">and the Document Area</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:32
msgid "The KDE Titlebar."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:33
msgid ""
"The &kde; Titlebar surrounds all applications run under &kde;. For more "
"information, please see the &kde; User Guide."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:36
msgid "The menu bar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:38
msgid ""
"The Menu Bar provides access to all of &kword;'s functions and options. Each "
"part of the &kword; menu bar is detailed in the section entitled: <link "
"linkend=\"basic-menubar\">The Basic Menu Bar</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:42
msgid "The Toolbars"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:43
msgid ""
"The Tool bars provide shortcuts to commonly used functions. &kword; uses 8 "
"tool bars, with similar functions grouped together."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:46
msgid "The Document Area."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:47
msgid "The document area consists of:"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
msgid "Horizontal and Vertical Rulers"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
msgid ""
"The rulers can be used to help you layout your document. For more "
"information on Rulers, see <link linkend=\"rulers\">Using Rulers</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
#, fuzzy
msgid "Scroll bar"
msgstr "Drsnik"

#: index.docbook:49
msgid ""
"The scroll bars are used to move through a &kword; document quickly. The "
"&kword; scroll bar functions similar to all scroll bars in &kde; or "
"&Windows;."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
msgid "Tab Selector"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
msgid ""
"This is used to select and place tab stops in your document for easy "
"formatting. For more information on tab stops, see the section entitled "
"<link linkend=\"tab-stops\">Using Tab Stops</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
msgid "Document View"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:49
msgid ""
"This is the area of the screen which is used to enter text. It shows you the "
"current status of your document, and allows you to adjust frames, select "
"text, and cut and paste text."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Format Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid ""
"This toolbar has commonly used features for formatting your text and "
"paragraph borders. Features on this toolbar include boldface and italic "
"text, superscripted text, and adding a border to your paragraph"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "File Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "This toolbar is used to load, save, print and start new documents"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Insert Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid ""
"This toolbar is used to add new text frames to your document. You can also "
"add graphics, tables or formulas to your document with this toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Edit Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid ""
"This toolbar is for common editing functions such as cut, paste, undo, redo, "
"find and spell check"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Paragraph Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid ""
"This toolbar is used to insert pictures, clip-art or special characters in "
"your document."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Table Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "This toolbar is used to add or remove rows or columns from tables."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Borders Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "This toolbar is used to add or remove borders surrounding paragraphs."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "Formula Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:87
msgid "This toolbar is used to add or remove formulas and their components."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:159
msgid "Using Rulers"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:161
msgid ""
"Along the left and top edges of the Document area, are a horizontal and a "
"vertical ruler."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:164
msgid "These rulers measure from the top left edge of the page."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:166
msgid ""
"Each ruler has a bright area surrounded by a dark area. The bright area "
"shows the size and location of the currently selected frame on that page. As "
"you change frames, the bright area changes to reflect the new frame's "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:178
msgid "The ruler can measure the page in 3 units of measure:"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:180
msgid "Millimeters (mm)"
msgstr "Milimetri (mm)"

#: index.docbook:180
msgid "Points (pt)"
msgstr "Toƒçke (pt)"

#: index.docbook:180
msgid "Inches (in)"
msgstr "Palci (inch)"

#: index.docbook:186
msgid ""
"To change the units of the ruler, place the mouse cursor over one of the "
"rulers (either one), and click with the <mousebutton>right</mousebutton> "
"button on your mouse."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:190
msgid ""
"Select your choice from the sub-menu. You will notice both rulers change to "
"the new unit of measure."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:193
msgid ""
"You may also notice two vertical arrows (one pointed up, the other pointed "
"down), on the left side of the bright area of the horizontal ruler. These "
"are used to adjust the margin of a paragraph. For more information, see the "
"section entitled <link linkend=\"format-para\">Formatting Paragraphs.</link>"
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:199
msgid ""
"Finally, you may see some black marks, which are not part of the ruler. They "
"may appear as L shaped, a Reverse-L, an Upside-down T, or an Upside-down T "
"with a dot in it. These are location of tab stops. For more information see "
"the section entitled <link linkend=\"tab-stops\">Using Tab Stops</link>."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:205
msgid ""
"To quickly format the page layout, you can right mouse click on either "
"ruler. A small sub menu will appear. Simply select Page Layout, and the Page "
"Layout Dialog box will appear."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:211
msgid "If you don't want the rulers in your document area, they can be switched off."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:211
msgid ""
"Simply select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>"
"Configure Kword</guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the Menu Bar. Click on the "
"<guibutton>Interface</guibutton> button. The top check box will let you "
"toggle the rulers on and off."
msgstr ""
